        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:02PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brevard, or near Looking Glass, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brevard, Etowah, Looking Glass, Dupont State Forest, Little River In
Transylvania County, Penrose, North Transylvania, and Forge Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
